<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 06 at 3:22PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central
Liberty, southwestern Hill and north central Chouteau Counties
through 400 PM MDT...
At 320 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Joplin, or 7 miles east of Chester, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Joplin, Inverness, Kenilworth and Rudyard.
This includes the following highways...
Highway 2 between mile markers 325 and 342.
Highway 87 between mile markers 57 and 62.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
